There's some friends that will always be in my heart and always be special to me. But I've also been learning there are moments we just have to let go and move on from certain things

On one hand I feel like I'm drifting apart from people I knew... But on the other, I feel like I'm just learning to let go?  It's like I'm free from something, it'd an odd feeling when it comes to this situation in particular. But I'm not too mad about it.
It's a bit funny cuz I feel like I'm just... leaving the past behind, in a sense. I've been bonding more with other friends, I've been meeting new people and made some great new friendships.

Honestly just wanted to rant and get it out of my head cuz I've been noticing it more and more and just thinking about it. But at the same time I'm meeting new people and make new friends and I feel so excited about it
But at the same time I already expected it to happen, so it bothers me less than it usually would. I guess it's just a matter of time and slowly getting back into that closeness again.

I also feel like I've always been the one initiating the convos most of the time too. And now that I am also busy and doing my own thing we've been interacting less and less. I don't think our friendship will die or anything it's just a bit weird and a bit of a bummer for now
It's just been harder and harder to match interests, and take some time to talk about stuff and hangout even if just online. Now whenever I try I just feel... odd.

Ah yes, that lovely feeling of drifting apart from someone you really like. So lovely.
Just been feeling more and more distant from one of my best friends lately. And it's a bit of an odd feeling cuz I kinda knew it'd happen, but it's still a bit sad.

And as someone now in an open-relationship and understanding herself as poly more and more, it is something I wanna learn more about, read/see represented more in media and art. And I do wanna bring it to my own art too.

There's a lot I wanna talk about in my next few projects. Themes, relationships, character concepts... part of the things I like to include in my stories are those social commentaries and to explore those personal and emotional experiences

I did have an AD/Nudes account for a while (that I never shared here) but it's been nuked and I don't know if I'd ever give it a try again XD
Photos and vid do help with self-confidence and whatnot (And I do have an exhibitionist side)
I'll just stick to art for now tho XD
I wanna redesign my sona and draw her a lot more. Cuz at the end of the day, it is myself represented in my own art. And I wanna explore a lot through that.

There's still a lot I want to do and experience, there's a lot to still learn about myself, and a lot of fears to overcome, but I'm getting there. And thanks to all who follow me through that journey. I hope we can learn together and inspire one another ❤️

My art, the friends I have now by my side, and a lot of fellow artists who inspire me so much, are all the things that helped me get where I am with a much healthier mind. And I'm so grateful and happy
I've learned to enjoy my friendships better, to enjoy my relationship, to never be scared to show love and affection to those around me. To be confident about myself, my passions and my art.

I've learned a lot about myself. I'm still learning. For most of my life I've been trapped in a shell cuz the world was scary and unforgiving. And now I can finally take a leap and just... live. Experience things I've either been denied, or denied myself of out of fear.

And a lot of my journey to overcome all those things, to get to a better place, is thanks to my art, and how I interact with art. How other artists share of those same things, to see people like me portrayed and represented

A lot of times, the world will have you believe that you're not worthy of any of it. I had people tell me that, being trans, I wasn't better for anything than a quick fuck, disposable, a dirty secret. I've been scared of showing my body to others. It was torture

It was a long journey to accept myself, to embrace myself, and feel free. To enjoy my body, or even my face. To accept I can be alluring, sexy, and enjoy myself without fear. That I can love and be loved. All of those things are so hard to handle

I think the toughest part of my transition was actually realizing I was trans, to begin with. Because there is no representation. Because the most the media would have me believe is I'd end up selling my body on the streets against my will.

There's a lot I still wanna explore with my art and future projects, partially because it helps me understand myself better, partially because I hope to inspire and give others something they can relate to, resonate with
The more I figure out myself, my interests and passions, my desires and the things I want, the more I get this feeling of freedom. I guess this whole account is partially responsible for it all.

But I've also came a very, veeery long way when it comes to my self-stem and security. I won't say it's perfect and that there aren't day anymore where dysphoria just weighs over me
But I really learned to love my body more and overcome those insecurities

I do joke a lot about self indulging through my art, even tho it's true, but honestly drawing porn and sexy characters it's incredibly satisfying and fulfilling. Especially when you got those moments where you just understand anatomy or a particular pose and feel proud

Kinda related to the previous thread/rant but tbh I just wanna vent out and rant about it a bit
But honestly so much has changed for the better for me since I began embracing my adult/sexual side/interests with less fear
@chuffaholic Can I just say tho, you've got the most incredible art for him. Every piece you show is just breathtaking or incredibly cute and fun

People have different tastes, comfort zones, and needs. They should all be able to pursue their interests safely, so long it's not hurting anyone.
Bottom line is: don't be a fucking dick

Sex and body positivity and incredibly important, and a lot of people in the fandom find empowerment and confidence in all of the adult stuff they get into. Enjoying sex is not a horrible sin that makes you a deviant. Not enjoying it doesn't make you a boring prude

In the end my point is: instead of trying to prove to anyone the fandom isn't "weird or just about adult stuff", we should probably be more worried about making it fun and safe to everyone, and encourage a healthy environment for people to pursue their interests.

It's one thing to be concerned about the consent of a certain situation, or if that friend of yours might be addicted and doing things unhealthily. But to go after people who are just enjoying themselves? That's just stupid
Again, I am not saying everyone should enjoy the adult and sexual stuff. Some people don't enjoy it and it's fine. I am saying people who don't like it shouldn't bother those who do for petty reasons

And I think that's the line. Is anyone being hurt by it? Is there misconduct, abuse of any sort, or a lack of consent? Cuz if it's consenting adults having their fun, people seriously need to fucking CHILL and step down from fictitious moral higher ground

But I see a lot of people worried about adult accounts, or trying to explain to the rest of the internet "We're not that weird/cringe!"
When honestly, you don't have to prove anyone anything. Those things others deem 'cringe' is just people having their fun without hurting others

Every place, every group, every community and fandom has bad apples. I will once again say I am not pretending the  fandom doesn't have any problems. I know how many we have, how many problematic people we've had to deal with.

We should stop being so desperate to paint the image a good Christian Household™️ to those outside.
A lot of people find comfort and confidence on the adult side of the fandom. People discover more about themselves, see themselves represented in art, and more

A lot of the fandom and a lot of this adult content also has a very much needed and positive side of sexual and bodily positivity. Now, I'm not pretending there aren't bad people or bad content. But if we're gonna talk about the fandom as a whole and how people enjoy it+

The thing is, it's one thing not to enjoy sexual content as a whole or prefer to avoid adult stuff. All of that is fine. Just like for those who do enjoy it, there are safe, healthy and very positive ways to engage

The problem is trying to paint adult stuff as inherently wrong.

But to try and justify everything to outsiders or even those internal justifications is just... There's something wrong there.
Sex is natural, it's part of life, and it can be the healthiest thing. There's nothing wrong with a good portion of the fandom being about it

Let's all be honest here. The majority of us are consenting adults who enjoy adult/sexual stuff. There are a lot of problems in the fandom, but I'm always glad to see people worried about fighting back and making it a safer place for all

And a lot of times these people are concerned with addressing the "cringe stuff" and saying "Oh the porn is not the majority of the fandom! Don't be weirded out! It's not all sex!"
But I think there's a few problems with trying to say it like that

A lot of time in places outside the furry fandom, like when some non-furry youtuber makes anything related to them, or forum posts etc etc, you'll always see the famous comment
"Oh but the weird part of the fandom is really just a minority!" and the likes

Y'know there's something that still bothers me deeply in this Fandom when it comes to the adult side. More specifically is how some people seem to deal poorly with it. And it mostly comes to "telling people outside the fandom about the the fandom"

So yeah expect a lot of new characters related to the MYZ setting dropping real soon XD besides designing them, I might have some fun drawing some silly interactions and making short strips for funsies

And each Tribe is very fun and unique on its own too. I just really wanna set up a game where players can just take their time to explore the dynamics between Animal Tribes, what it means to live and Paradise Valley to then find their own reason to stand up and fight

The whole 1984 vibe is quite interesting mixed with the survivalism of post-apocalypse and the sort of tribal culture that's usually born from settlements of these settings. A mix of tradition vs rebellion, peace and war, standing up against those mysterious powerful overlords

And when it comes to Genlab Alpha, it's incredible. It's not really furry bait surprisingly, but rather a very fun and interesting take on anthro animals on a post-apoc setting with strong themes and discussions and a fun world to explore

It's a fun and quite refreshing take on post-apoc stuff if I may say so, and I just like all the survival mechanics, how narrative driven the exploration is, and the whole system for maintaining and expanding settlements too. Also NPC relations, which is always my favourite part

Also trust me when I say, everyone should give Mutant Year Zero and the Genlab Alpha expansion a read, if anything for the pretty art. But even if you don't plan on running it or run TTRPGs, that book is just a joy to read. It's such an interesting setting

For now I'm only running the base game tho, and I'm yet to run a Genlab Alpha game. And tho I do wanna go a little more in-depth with NPCs, I feel like planning stuff for this game is just very relaxing and easy. I can just sit down and have ideas and it's very satisfying

A lot of the planning is done through the map itself and not even shown to the players until they find it, and I'm finding that it's better not to have way too many special zones right off the bat, or the map just feels way too cluttered. If every zone is special, none is

A lot of it can really be set up very fast of quickly generated on demand during the game thanks to all the tools the book gives ya. And for the first time I don't have to sit down and prepare a massive google docs detailing every bit of the map, history and whatnot

Despite the fact I have some sort of obsession for overcomplicating any project and way too many ideas for NPCs, running Mutant: Year Zero has been a blessing cuz it's so much nicer to set up and plan when it comes to campaigns

It's in the smallest things, y'know? Those daily and mundane thingies from our day-to-day lives that we just take from granted, so much we don't think about it. But then you have a character forced to confront what he's lost, and it's the smallest things that hit the hardest.

The reason I'm tweeting this is I think we don't say those things often enough, especially to people we care about. I've been incredibly blessed with the friends I have, and they've been helping me a lot. And I've been doing my best for them too

I don't know who needs to listen this today. But I want you all out there to remember: you are incredibly valid. It's not wrong to feel stuff, and it's not wrong to open up. Sometimes life feels way too hard and lonely - but I know you can do it. You valid and you matter a lot.

And this was another episode of me ranting about TTRPGs, tune in later tonight for some lizard drawings
Might even make a stream, who knows!

I really wanna explore the whole potential of Genlab Alpha in a game that fully focuses on the animals but is not completely bound by the metaplot of the base game or the Paradise Valley metaplot. Like just throw them furries in the wasteland and see what happens

Honestly I'd also love to set up a Twitch channel for TTRPG Actual plays, but I don't have enough English speaking friends that play 😔
I just think it'd be a lot of fun

Honestly to all of you who enjoy TTRPGs and DnD and the likes, I definitely recommend you go take a good read of Mutant: Year Zero and the Genlab Alpha Expansion. It's AMAZING. It's slowly becoming my favorite RPG book for sure
Find some new hope in a desolate world left behind by your mysterious ancestors. Just furries surviving and trying to build something new, with cool mutant powers in the mix. God, that'd be so fun

Tho being honest if there's one thing I'd love to run right now? MYZ Genlab Alpha. But like, I'd really like to make a full on setting with just the animals, full on post-apoc furry TTRPG, surviving the wastes, trying to make your own new settlement+
I'd still love to one day play as my Hexblade Tabaxi tho. This drawing is so old but I still love it a lot. She was adopted by a Dragonborn blacksmith and raised as one 😌 https://t.co/Aslpb8hMAE

I'd definitely love to join a game that's more narrative-driven, less war-game-like and more "Let's enjoy the cool setting and make our own story". I'm just someone who prefers when the game is focused on the players and their characters
Especially if you go looking through Roll20. Last time I was in a DnD game it was full on combat nearly every session and zero char development and it was just so tiring

For me the whole dungeon crawl part and extensive combat are just incredibly painfully boring. I'm way too narrative and roleplay driven. Now, I KNOW there are games like that out there. But they're not easy to find usually

Listen DnD has incredibly cool concepts, settings, races and potential
It's just hard for me to find games that run the way I like to play
Friend telling me about the DnD setting he's preparing and I'm here like "Damn that sounds so fucking awesome" and then I actually think about the system and just want to die instead 🥲

And then have a friend call me out for writing fanfic about Charon from Fallout 3 and then dreaming about a massively tall Nosferatu 😓

Listen I'm not saying I happen to like big monster-like men
I'm not denying either
Good morning to me and me alone for dreaming with a big vampire man flirting with me in the shower 😌

Alright rant is over back to furry porn I guess

The key here is group understanding: everyone has to be on the same page about things and accept that sometimes those things will change mid-game. Maybe a player will say fine to a thing and three sessions later they'll say stop- when they do, you s t o p

Hell yeah I'll narrate consequences to poor choices, and of course some things will be horrible- so long it doesn't run over what players are comfortable with. The world is already shit so why not tell a story about personal winnings then? Fucking hell

And hell, I run fucking World of Darkness. Vampire and Werewolf. The whole thing is about personal horror and how the world is terrible. You know what I never did running those? Sacrifice player comfort and story for fucking grittiness

But what I really cannot accept is someone forcibly throwing a plot on their players because they think the cool story concept is more fun than the player's comfort. I've seen  it happen, I had it happen to me. It's NOT fun
Psssh, here's a tip: your plot is less important than player story. And trust me, it's a lot more fun when you let them go about their stuff and change the story through their choices.

Honestly this is wild to me because as a GM/ST myself, I worry too much about my players and what they want. I just can't see the fun of writing a whole ass script to be followed. Let. Your player. have. FUN

I've seen people praise their own egos because they valued "realism" so much over a good story and player enjoyment. Hell I've had a ST thrown a fucking pregnancy plot on my character after I've specifically said I wasn't comfortable with that. Because "cool concept"

Lemme explain: I just hate it when GMs/STs just decide telling their own little story is more important than that of the players and what they are trying to do. ESPECIALLY when it crosses over personal comfort and logic
